This article is a presidential proclamation issued by President Barack Obama in 2009. The proclamation honors the victims of the tragedy at Fort Hood, Texas. It expresses condolences and prayers for the service members, civilians, and families affected by the events. The proclamation orders that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at various locations, including the White House, public buildings, military posts, naval stations, and naval vessels, as a mark of respect. The flag is to be flown at half-staff until sunset on November 10, 2009. The proclamation also extends the same order to United States embassies, consular offices, military facilities, and naval vessels abroad.